sentences: Zsuzsa Mary also known as Zsuzsi Mary (Born Zsuzsanna Mary; 13 October 1947 – 24 December 2011) was a Hungarian pop singer.
She appeared first time on stage in 1965, later she finished on the first place in the Hungarian Television's song contest, the  Táncdalfesztivál, with the song "Mama" (Mom) in 1968.

In 1969, she married György Klapka, and soon after emigrated with her husband.
They divorced in 1987, but maintained a good relationship.
Mary came out as bisexual in 2008.
She committed suicide on Christmas Eve, 2011, aged 64.
